content.description: This is a short, two bolt route, with old bolts and loose rock. A cool height dependent jump start establishes you on jugs and a bolt on an inclusion block. Move up to a ledge and second bolt to the top.
content.protection: Protection bolts are original drop ins. Two modern bolts at anchor. Bring tat to rap.
content.location: Located on the SE corner of the formation. The first bolt can be hard to see from the ground.

content.description: A short, one bolt face to the top of the Camel's Foot. Regular Camelback crumble. The bolt looks good.
content.protection: A single newish wedge bolt. No anchor at top. Belay from bolted anchor across on other side of the formation.
content.location: Western end of the Camel's Foot. One bolt about 20' up is visible from ground.

content.description: The Camel's Foot is a small feature in the center of the Camel's head. There are two short routes to the top. Nice views, afternoon shade and cool position make up for short, crumbly routes.
